  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In our city, I would say things began changing approximately 1939, 1940, when the Slovakian Republic came out with various laws that influenced the Jewish populations, restrictions such as Jewish people were not allowed to walk on the street after 6 o'clock, such as wearing a star or a band, such as Jewish people were now allowed to have only two suits-- limit of two, and various restrictions.",
      "word_count": 68
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they came out, these laws, were repeated-- repeated very often.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Every time, they come out with something new that one cannot have-- restriction-- restricting in banking, restricting in how much money one can own, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was kind of young, of course, when-- when the era of that you're questioning me right now, was when I was approximately 14 years old.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And our youth were not as sophisticated as American youth is today, with the television and media and so forth.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The first time I heard about Hitler is, I remember when the newspaper came out with the headline that Hitler has occupied Austria.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's the first time that I realized who's Hitler, and what's Hitler, and-- and we're start talking about it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not favorably.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, we had many people who were working for the government, like policeman and-- and officials that were in various government positions, used to come to us at least once a year around Christmas time, and my father would fill up their bottles with wine as presents, as gifts, of course.",
      "word_count": 55
    }
  ],
